Moving slowly, alert for any kind of trap, Cody stepped into the doorway to the room. He was nevertheless shocked when a voice hailed him from only a few feet away. “Aloha, Cody! Welcome to Tjiwideg's delicatessen!” The man, presumably Tjiwidej himself, beamed at Cody. Cody's first thought was that he had no idea how to pronounce the man's name, even after hearing it directly from him. His second was to wonder how the man knew his name.
